ast.name: RPN Calculator
ast.comment:
A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation.

REG toggles between one and ten addressable storage registers. "FIX . number" toggles between "," and "." as the decimal symbol. All other functions work as on HP calculators.

Perhaps the next step should be a help function. :-)

2012-06-04: Fixed a bug with detecting keystrokes.

app.comment: A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). REG toggles between one and ten addressable storage registers. "FIX . number" toggles between "," and "." as the decimal symbol. 2012-09-16: PLOT also shows spikes to the original data points of a correlation analysis. New LIST function. In the next version, you will be able to switch correlation functions *after* entering data. Please post any bugs in the forum (of course, there couldn't be any ;-)

app.comment: A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-18: ROUND now rounds to display settings, as stated in online help (always rounded to whole numbers previously). Fixed y^ calculation for y=ax+bx³ correlation function. Additional quadratic trigonometric correlation function (13 in total now). Plus some minor refinements.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-30: The calculator is fully programmable, very similar to the classic programmable HP pocket calculators. Please see the help pages for detailed information.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-11-10: Used a superscript Chi Unicode character to get nicer yᵡ, eᵡ and 10ᵡ keys. Please note that programs using the previous y^x, e^x or 10^x functions must be edited or will just ignore the functions. Please just delete the old program step and insert the new one.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-12-10: New ABS and VIBR functions (removed M- to make room). New SET function for customizing the calculator, including keyboard and program speed. SHOW displays program listing and can copy it to the clipboard.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-12-29: You can store and manage multiple programs with names in a library using the SET function - the replacement for a magnetic card reader! Plus several refinements and improvements.
